DCDCDC;border-top:none;direction:ltr;font-size:0px;padding:0;text-align:center;"><!--[if mso | IE]><table role="presentation" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="" style="vertical-align:top;width:598px;" ><![endif]--><div class="mj-column-per-100 mj-outlook-group-fix" style="font-size:0px;text-align:left;direction:ltr;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top;width:100%;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td style="border-top:1px solid #999999;padding-bottom:4px;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td style="border-top:1px solid #999999;padding-bottom:4px;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td style="border-top:1px solid #999999;padding-bottom:4px;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td style="border-top:1px solid #999999;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td align="left" class="text text-with-border" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:8px 16px 16px;word-break:break-word;"><div style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:13px;line-height:1;text-align:left;color:#000000;"><h2 style="margin: 0; font-size: 24px; color: #121212;">My picks</h2></div></td></tr><tr role="presentation"><td style="padding-bottom:8px;border-top:2px dashed #999999;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td align="center" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px 16px;word-break:break-word;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" style="border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0px;"><tbody><tr><td style="width:566px;"><img alt="Palestinian film-maker and Oscar winner for the documentary “No Other Land” Hamdan Ballal poses for a picture with his Oscar, as he recovers after Israeli settlers attacked him at home, in his village of Susya in the south of the occupied West Bank on March 26, 2025. Israeli police released Ballal on March 25, after detaining him a day earlier for “hurling rocks” following what activists described as an attack by settlers in the occupied West Bank." height="auto" src="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9assuTJHoR_xtxJtNZ-864UldtA1nMwk1oq3l155bS6uyQexoNlvkXzVe2V7UOVg9cTKqM6W_UptWA8TaDahVfmTSVxGedS_tr0A62ZZNVDYsqOcfLIYyHHU5DQYFAL_6iG0Zu5o15-k7jD4OpkmNX3kA9jy6YUuwkDpAaqAFhZrrD-6IcFujuBmFk_pAToIvO-AirpSUYn4bXLiOZjymKH1qyFpfvv76lcb8fBIHHy4Z/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t33/h001.3N5WXkCOmrYsT1MNYMf8nA5Yvucp_Pyz31MtIuUshDE style="border:0;display:block;outline:none;text-decoration:none;height:auto;width:100%;font-size:13px;" width="566"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td align="left" class="text" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px;word-break:break-word;"><div style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:22px;text-align:left;color:#121212;"><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Last week I mentioned how I was blown away by <em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">No Other Land</strong></em>, the Oscar-winning documentary about the destruction of villages in the West Bank. On Monday, one of the film’s co-directors, Hamdan Ballal, was attacked by armed settlers before being arrested by IDF soldiers. After he was released, Ballal <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBNfMDKFRfOEsk3CaiO1OPbbIU26sERcR0Wvpt5CxOTnSd7Bi-QKrkXiEfcnpsN1qBakxu0ftSeQZ9FKhtfOl8EMT3aFaMsa6y1HdNS_iNA0zxVSsZtg59IXOI30zeRNCJ-0mLfvWzsyx8IWG2WFp6xtkTWHMaqSE_IabzxSbvN7cJ30Tj6cc6Ad044zq6Dgk_BMzSVyKMZ2zpQVjQ2hyohfZh3gigxD01M5leIREjNGA98m3PG7NcJpz8Ue9FqfEPWp2gUtIzf_OVQaK2SbVBLBoxZ5FfwYevhXf_4E7BhMyfVVMdgOd5PkeLVgoUMcNwJw4cxR036C4st3YSe3CfJV/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t34/h001.kRYcJy6TYkNVzQeyU1u_eFHZzO8g7Wjo1iPvDcNGgj4 style="color: #0077B6;">gave an account of his ordeal</a> to correspondent Lorenzo Tondo, who also appeared <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBPKPngssJVVWBHdpoM-VOQfW_u7IR3g1f1BEPVnxGqgk51k82qIgKUi27IerUOpZ2vp5x87-L8LxpazAttmU2O1nD6wpQAkeXBnKqq6sFoNPSx1rf21jMMdezeu3-Zot6kpS8x25pJYc-fXZobGy8CnVuqCu_RgNW3ZVVPqBlCHDS-sbgtWhk89XoC1jN00pglE8Dae1bgZswvjpxiwHWDEXQG7t4zNF2FIrhaLQImOsxt8K53MPDIWz0dmL3anubN2BBFeiAcCz1Frmsgb1lKAqqbwEv8RcgsXxNBNXWo0p59qI0YukxFJ6LR3E6uiKr5LOQSWfrqAxnlwLKBSHMaT/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t35/h001.t03tXtQRUjRGTydSB3Th4ogkhBsIGpnYJUmQJjF7juo style="color: #0077B6;">on Friday’s Today in Focus</a> to discuss the incident. Ofer Cassif, a member of Israel’s Knesset who has spent years tackling settler violence in the West Bank, <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBPmb_62cBCcT0p1ftGfLF2P4Zxkx3kuRTJ12BqQ1FfjC7xyjMJ3r763yPTnsxo_fnHjWXrEqI80ke3REiORyO0zKQdKhq7Y5f4G5eqBPr5ZLEvuGkPW3KIJFHnfcflTjwvi6xn6D6hapKVM0AzaYU0pDvMHtocrCHlVJdB_3ZpkI6A5sS-jgsmICxz4xwt1clCXfVKeu44B4KSFSLqlsiB7jsJOZKYkdEzME8eDr4OMZkffvQtOT-nlIkncqXEVqZ-gmypM8ZC8gIL-4E5UJ4S3IEQ9f1R1ZuuCB6OYJGyyEQ/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t36/h001.91fqV1cBxrRs9v-yQo40HuIiRLwioPsQAw0H6kECbcg style="color: #0077B6;">pointed out</a> that it has taken an Oscar-winner’s detention for the world to pay attention to what is happening.</p><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">We have closely followed events in <em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">Turkey</strong></em> as thousands took to the streets for days of protests over the arrest of Istanbul’s mayor Ekrem İmamoğlu, the opposition candidate selected to stand against Recep Tayyip Erdoğan in the country’s next presidential election. Ruth Michaelson, Sami Kent and Michael Safi <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBPKPngssJVVWBHdpoM-VOQfrIGh2Ltj8QRwoYXdrkxLNBCz-BUrDLfA-HNEvMHIGIcIrSDLWlz6nUXQWXJ9dnFb46DFTfEkWXg9uP68kb95nsNyDiOEBy8mwxbzk8NAgmH5iCQ5oSHaOH1vTYHz6WoBxWbGdEhwie2uTgAxTEqCjlWTY6eOicbw83HPgzrqs0ma4tka_2k87vuqB_1cL2waD0g3BzgImOseRDhszMmLAehL1obrRl55GOGMuahFd4XAIfQRbDcT4VrP21wIjpELtlQH8VWQitA3u-ZDMXv88Q/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t37/h001.eyjBQcYKyrEx5fXD91wKrq6knXh_MJ-ryoqKo76vVTk style="color: #0077B6;">discussed the protests on a fascinating edition of Today in Focus</a>. As journalists were arrested and deported by the authorities, Ruth reported on the <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBNfMDKFRfOEsk3CaiO1OPbbOfI7ZkBqy6_T3D_Z0i8iFvNwF5mCpadjujsYKQoe5whHNQYPirIIxZLgv0r9FPYvnXZrM3z7ocTYAJBZnSel8W0qNn6yjywAH2dqpt2dWCcw4p7JXAhzldF9WUWP3RIc7dlTIJCzLdMxdPlp8Jf0X0dbx6FYTQTMT67enzmcdhH_YMeQXb3CVCe3aq6v1gGiIz0CbFJfrAyGoVpfuFLIAWlmIHx-f6QuerOIB4b7VbThQI9IFjJWXof-9JpSGNBdbiNjP-3sU51omA7Eq5iBB2zowBwkiShnQjM4v4UqY4U/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t38/h001.oGQ6hbae665D4FSPd2bdEwXaIriFK_sglB930sEDxzo style="color: #0077B6;">gulf in coverage</a> between pro-government media and the small slice of independent sources. Writer Ece Temelkuran wrote about the youthful energy of street protest that is <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBPmb_62cBCcT0p1ftGfLF2PN49-lp590yA9sk4NiO59E-FZ5tFiEPSx62bejKfU6kPkej9Nv_US09DJSerrrH98AU6gHJptnoSsVasFfVAG1uiunfvUjYTFPY36NaCFtTjfHp2Cg0TqG1RlZsH02e3445_tcG_v_Ld-N-s7mt3-q5fUVK4y9GYveiXpKNxzr8iMkqAMuVkUu5QdDGz0FlfvU6mFnQgo6bMEVQtKXsoobr4VBIKT4oxZA7cl0sBpG4b7ODyu4MCLiNuEOky7cHHy6ZgjlRtRhr9y0G50aaaLiA/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t39/h001.Bdx3xR_lYBGc6zOn0fzB-f6vq2ecpa2yAn9DE0JXq60 style="color: #0077B6;">breathing life back into failing progressive parties</a>.</p><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Australia’s Labor prime minister, <em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">Anthony Albanese</strong></em>, has called a federal election for 3 May. The team in Australia was ready, with an <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theg