rder-spacing:0px;"><tbody><tr><td style="width:566px;"><img alt="charred gnocchi, purple sprouting broccoli and gorgonzola." height="auto" src="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9assuTJHoR_xtxJtNZ-864Um1ZYkLbd3CFSBz6P8vtsSQw_8aDjGTiw9jaKd7YjqV0biWLXUVy7-Axr1AxNC-_IgDJr3RUfoakI3K4FD07AE4qkaMdnfk45JR1WNd6hbrJHhI9koeWoIgdb1Ox1r-BktNQGl6i_ZIUQPbrDgz71y5MCbqXx9_Hz3T6wEN1AFGi4EURNYW8bU4neYf2N34Ph6sUdxH1FB-NegaeO0iuRXl/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t71/h001.pQ9JpNsQcmgZX5Is0n3ulowvy0P2tPDYhklJ6aEZtb4 style="border:0;display:block;outline:none;text-decoration:none;height:auto;width:100%;font-size:13px;" width="566"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td align="left" class="text" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px;word-break:break-word;"><div style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:22px;text-align:left;color:#121212;"><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;"><em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">Cook this</strong></em> | <strong>Charred gnocchi, purple sprouting broccoli and gorgonzola</strong></p><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Frying and grilling steers gnocchi away from their familiar doughiness and instead gives them a delicious, nutty edge. This <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBPUL98g18zIAaVxD_-mqY8Wyuke-2xdVJxaWCWocuJ7Qq7oubBtMTCmVFnAPPc-hcf55AAg2aTk1te6qM-H4zvzpW-Ib94-58gZ2mKGSnEy8oqiQkidxm2ICU7unKS-N7986w9PAAFHZAx_uVgg5EO71xEVfgHvzzoA6NWLYvrPsWeCA0sF15fAX18Kz0AjVXzQGzygjSebY7Cwk5VzRxipE36xlezQ51nVJ8LfMKnGW3jK4H_z4gAK95qUT0yF8KFY9Z9607L-lHoB4ZTg7R_WaQzfWu2sc03bHfTNlTZbv8b3xMn3ieSXZ0j3UCk2OmQ/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t72/h001.qw4QdOzbAtFN2PyNvu22Fi4yE-i3tOKkaExpQoKvVLI style="color: #0077B6;">recipe</a> by Georgina Hayden is a fancy-feeling dish that is incredibly easy to throw together.<br></p></div></td></tr><tr><td align="center" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px 16px;word-break:break-word;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" style="border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0px;"><tbody><tr><td style="width:566px;"><img alt="Humpback whale mother and calf on the New Caledonian breeding grounds. A composite image for the Full Story podcast." height="auto" src="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9assuTJHoR_xtxJtNZ-864Ulz3LKkjGYV491MNfNHl-wjCcHY9nvNQNAUikxJwrH31w7YJcQzNtjoxkoFCxDExEBguIJFZvvHPTH7-nH3B67VNewNr1LBCApIRyN9R_-yliYAcOGRJVV9AS8qlCF8QF3gzZg6aUNqZiex1oH5PGog5UeH3_rpxjJ-2ThItZSiFjOsWuA8P0gwwVFd_Qf053poNtFXb_LyKHGqX_MaYok6/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t73/h001.DbmlnKODGoq5PTLIwdoLGjESG2yLGEPy8YZwB3doACo style="border:0;display:block;outline:none;text-decoration:none;height:auto;width:100%;font-size:13px;" width="566"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td align="left" class="text" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px;word-break:break-word;"><div style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:22px;text-align:left;color:#121212;"><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;"><em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">Listen to this</strong></em> | <strong>The language of whale song</strong></p><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Researchers have discovered that humpback whale song is strikingly similar to human language. Dr Jenny Allen, an expert in whale song structure at Griffith University, Queensland, <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBMwXgobXWT7BO5FdExlac2o-6jCgetJCH17WoSeZcWz4gLu8krrAL3OK4xRj_Lu0gGKnM1zEkOOM5HIxAhZEDrVKkKMXIp2fhk2zVveoTo0uH40_vGNE_YAhT05cwWVXPRn-hiRcV96_OsHsYZoWnX92G2xF_wb1NdWllAutXwhMHDJ767-9DQUVqSF7nUmGtx3tsbb2KQtd2guecaQw3F6nFE52E4LGePFl_gEJ5QkM4pYYQjFzc4-HJnxPjEpQ8EinRthoZuvg0Aeilg-H2ShT4icLzXsld1_ZJozLQ5GfA/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t74/h001.zCg10o4Bk_IHjeKnNOLjhmEpvzvRhGTQ8Vnzu6k9BI0 style="color: #0077B6;">speaks to Reged Ahmad</a> about the years of recording, listening and analysing that led to this greater understanding of how humpback whales learn their tune.</p></div></td></tr><tr><td align="center" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px 16px;word-break:break-word;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" style="border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0px;"><tbody><tr><td style="width:566px;"><img alt="ShortOrder NetZero thumbnail J" height="auto" src="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9assuTJHoR_xtxJtNZ-864UkEbf3YYe8LR7zouThF-i00sKRFt3KniTsnS0DDMruBaQqRn3UuFo7KswZc2x6viRPyMtFtcWss3pG7BWGwe-OFN85U844uAb8kJW5k6BBWaHJPZjkb1zzBA62yG8QRSFoCcHpwZDKWSZrv5lMK1Ff6d0IWAnXis0LO8r5UxsyhulZs9ZR3Rvnw8JbaJZw2lbOegms9z4DyraDbAvN_FMdw/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t75/h001.WvIHxF6mprWpDi2zPgMny3f0RotmGLJXJx-OYp3a3NA style="border:0;display:block;outline:none;text-decoration:none;height:auto;width:100%;font-size:13px;" width="566"></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td align="left" class="text" style="background:#FFFFFF;font-size:0px;padding:0 16px;word-break:break-word;"><div style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:22px;text-align:left;color:#121212;"><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;"><em><strong style="color: #052962; font-style: normal; font-weight: 700;">Watch this</strong></em> | <strong>How countries cheat their net zero carbon targets</strong></p><p style="margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Net zero is a target that countries should be striving for to stop the climate crisis. But beyond the buzzword, it is a complex scientific concept – and if we get it wrong, the planet will keep heating. Biodiversity and environment reporter Patrick Greenfield <a href="https://ablink.editorial.theguardian.com/ss/c/u001.-maoMBGKBrIn6te6KzY9apUCjm_UVImAPea-qhHewBM3m8r9z1xmycoesx2ZCgQqtAqrlTFBHzWkgC3WR4QUxam_VEKA2VwnQH44VH_KCkcr525XupsKeiuyxHQoFO29FwXo6NYE0uYJfx1OuEvJYoJz9jkD7TLkfaTcmo3AP92u63YGVKjnBamfdNTQxUzYSIod43fFRlmY2wC0AUjeaGexNxC9Jg1bbJdlVP7b2EF4Vj4DjMbU5EhvQjkIgE4yaADkrHIqc_a422NhBhPeTJVVamzmTaqBEIC4i9juq_JcnAy7RyZV36r81AGz0OwzO3iCRhZ9j28xSU3KcYdU9A/4f7/u907YvKMT92Se6lYyXvnTw/t76/h001.CGIF16DIS0JLCLarTWQvwqj2BrAmGxilRae86xgV9P4 style="color: #0077B6;">explains</a> how a loophole in the 2015 Paris climate agreement allows countries to cheat their net zero targets through creative accounting, and how scientists want us to fix it.</p></div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><!--[if mso | IE]></td></tr></table><![endif]--></td></tr></tbody></table></div><!--[if mso | IE]></td></tr></table></td></tr><![endif]--> <table role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td><div style="height:20px;line-height:20px"> </div></td></tr></tbody></table><!--[if mso | IE]><tr><td class="" width="600px" ><table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="" role="presentation" style="width:600px;" width="600" ><tr><td style="line-height:0px;font-size:0px;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;"><![endif]--><div style="margin:0px auto;max-width:600px;"><table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" style="width:100%;"><tbody><tr><td style="border:1px solid #DCDCDC;border-top:none;direction:ltr;font-size:0px;padding:0;text-align:center;"><!--[if mso | IE]><table role="presentation" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="" style="vertical-align:top;width:598px;" ><![endif]--><div class="mj-column-per-100 mj-outlook-group-fix" style="font-size:0px;text-align:left;direction:ltr;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top;width:100%;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" role="presentation" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td style="border-top:1px solid #999999;padding-bottom:4px;background-color:#FFFFFF"></td></tr><tr><td style="border-top:1p